Subject: Re: Diagnostic Report (Log {{LOG_ID}})

Hi,

Thanks for sending a diagnostic report! To help you effectively, I need more details about what you're experiencing.

═══════════════════════════════════════
🔍 WHAT I NEED
═══════════════════════════════════════

1️⃣ SPECIFIC PROBLEM:
• Which device(s) aren't working?
• What exactly happens? (or doesn't happen?)
• Any error messages shown?

2️⃣ DEVICE MANUFACTURER IDs:
For each problematic device:
• Homey → Settings → Devices → [Device Name]
• Click ⚙️ (Settings) → Advanced → Zigbee information
• Copy "manufacturerName" value (e.g., "_TZ3000_xabckq1v", "TS0601")
• Share here

3️⃣ ACTIVE DIAGNOSTIC:
Current log may not show the issue. Please:
• Open Homey → Settings → Apps → Universal Tuya Zigbee
• Click 📊 Diagnostics
• ⚠️ BEFORE submitting:
  - Reproduce the issue (test device, trigger error, etc.)
  - Wait 30 seconds
• THEN submit with detailed message describing what you tested
• Share new log ID

═══════════════════════════════════════
⚡ QUICK CHECKS (Try These First)
═══════════════════════════════════════

1. Restart Homey:
   • Settings → System → Reboot
   • Wait 2 minutes for Zigbee mesh

2. Check device battery (if battery-powered)

3. Re-pair device:
   • Remove from Homey
   • Factory reset device
   • Pair within 2m of Homey
   • Wait 60s for full enrollment

4. Verify correct driver selected during pairing
